# ML Tools & Workflows — {{companyName}}

## When to Use
- Setting up ML experiment tracking (MLflow, W&B, Neptune)
- Managing ML pipelines and feature stores
- Working with notebooks and data exploration

## Experiment Tracking
- Log all hyperparameters, metrics, and artifacts
- Use consistent naming for experiments and runs
- Tag experiments with project, team, and objective metadata
- Compare runs systematically before promoting models

## Model Management
- Version models alongside training code
- Store model artifacts in a centralized registry
- Document model cards with performance metrics, data lineage, and known limitations
- Implement A/B testing frameworks for model comparison

## Best Practices
- Separate data preprocessing from model training code
- Use reproducible environments (Docker, conda lock files)
- Validate data quality before training pipelines
- Monitor model performance drift in production
